description.narrative: Since 2016, UNICEF has advocated for the expansion of ECE to reduce equity gaps. CO has contributed to the national and provincial policy through innovation, evidence generation for the development of quality standards, training policies for teachers and managers and communication to increase awareness of the importance of ECE. CO has contributed to improve the quality of education through self-assessment tools for schools and has supported programs to increase the quality of ECE in rural areas, reaching a total of 38,800 children.;Finally,UNICEF substantially contributed to COVID19 National response plan to mitigate the school lockdown impact on children. | Status:Met | As-of Date:18/08/2021
